      • validUser

        public static java.lang.Boolean validUser​(java.lang.String username,
                                          java.lang.String password)
                                   throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                          java.io.IOException
        Takes in the User's provided username and password String values and compares the pair against the existing entries within the users SQL table, also passes details to log the attempt and whether or not it was successful
        Parameters:
        username - the User's entered username String to be checked within the users SQL table in tandem with the entered password String
        password - the User's entered password String to be checked within the users SQL table in tandem with the entered username String
        Returns:
        the boolean result of if the provided username and password String combination exist together within the SQL database
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - thrown in case of SQL database issues
        java.io.IOException - thrown in case of log file creation/appending issues

      • loginAttempt

        public static void loginAttempt​(java.lang.String username,
                                java.lang.String date,
                                java.lang.String time,
                                boolean valid)
                         throws java.io.IOException
        Attempts to create or append entries to a log file detailing log in attempts to the application with details passed during the call of the method
        Parameters:
        username - the username String entered in the login attempt
        date - the date String of the login attempt
        time - the time String of the login attempt
        valid - a boolean representing whether the login attempt had been successful or not
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown in case of log file creation/appending issues
